comments.body:
Actually, it appears that you will also need to to run the following command after the {{mv}} before re-running {{build-reuters.sh}}

{{./bin/mahout seqdirectory \}}
{{  -i ./examples/bin/work/reuters-out/ \}}
{{  -o ./examples/bin/work/reuters-out-seqdir \}}
{{  -c UTF-8 -chunk 5}}

I'm testing a patch to fix build-reuters.sh to account for the new behavior ExtractReuters

Hmm, the Lucene ExtractReuters code has:
{code}
// First, extract to a tmp directory and only if everything succeeds, rename
    // to output directory.
    File outputDir = new File(args[1] + "-tmp");
    outputDir.mkdirs();
    ExtractReuters extractor = new ExtractReuters(reutersDir, outputDir);
    extractor.extract();
    // Now rename to requested output dir
    outputDir.renameTo(new File(args[1]));
{code}

So that indicates to me something else is wrong.  There shouldn't be a -tmp if all went well.

{quote}
Just curious, why the need to change from work to mahout-work?
{quote}

After running hadoop fs -ls a bunch of times and seeing first 'examples' and then 'work', I figured it would be nice to be a bit more specific as to the purpose of the directory.

{quote}
Hmm, Drew, I don't see the ClusterDump output after running this in local mode.
{quote}

Grant, I know at least once when I ran kmeans, it converged at the 9th iteration and thus cluster-10 was never written and cluster dump didn't produce output. It would be nice to be able to handle this case elegantly, but I wasn't certain how often something like this happens. If anyone else runs into this problem, a listing of the reuters-kmeans directory would be useful.

{quote}
If we commit this, do you all think this is about right such that we can continue with the release?
{quote}

Sean, I think this is ready to go, but I would feel most comfortable if we could have at least one other test. 

Any takers? Allan or Mat, if either of you are reading perhaps you could give it a whirl? 

Am I correct to assume this is the only blocker at this point?

{quote}
All I need now is to find how I can create my vector files to use kmeans.
{quote}

Allan, Do you subscribe to the mahout user mailing list? It would be appropriate to discuss that issue there.
